{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend the definition of \u2018looked after\u2019 children",
        "additional_details": "Children deserve protection from harm, to be gifted the best start to adulthood. For children in care, entering adulthood is naturally a challenging time. However, for many children in care who haven't acquired 'looked after child' status doors are closed, and accessing help is limited.\r\n\r\nChildren with Special Educational Needs, accommodated in Children\u2019s Homes through an LA's Education Functions, are not guaranteed 'looked after' status in law. This means they do not have access to an Independent Reviewing Officer, do not have to be visited by a Social Worker, and cannot access most care leaving services.",
        "background": "The Government should include children placed in accommodation under a local authority\u2019s education functions, including SEN children, within the definition of \u2018looked after\u2019 children.",
